entry.content:
This CL loads campaigns component at Demo Mode session when session

become active and launch Demo Mode app once both Demo Mode app component

and Growth Campaign component finish loading. The app will launch with

URL including the campaign payload to drive Demo Mode app customization

if there is a Demo Mode app campaign selected.

based on the payload passed from the URL.

alongs with loading Demo Mode app and resource component to make sure

that there is at least a version of campaign component available at

session start. This will also reduce the latency of launching the Demo

means the third party cookie is real blocked. In other words, we only

entry.title: [RWS] Move switch-parsing code to FPSParser; move LocalSetDecl to net/
entry.content:
This centralizes the parsing step with the rest of the parsing code;

and encodes the invariants that GlobalFirstPartySets expects the local

set declaration to satisfy, explicitly, by checking them directly in

the only nontrivial constructor of LocalSetDeclaration.



This makes the interface exposed by GlobalFirstPartySets safer, since

it is now impossible to call ApplyManuallySpecifiedSet with an invalid

map of entries.



It also makes it easier to evolve the internal representation of a

LocalSetDeclaration if needed, since they are now only constructed via

a default ctor or the FPSParser; and their internals are only accessed

by the GlobalFirstPartySets class.

entry.title: [CompositeClipPathAnimations] Fix crash for animation fill forward
entry.content:
This CL fixes a crash that occurred when animation-fill-mode is set to forwards. This crash occurs because invalidating the paint property data on the animated element is contingent upon the clip path data actually changing, which might not happen if the system has had a frame on main thread recently enough that the clip path hasn't changed - or if the animation is using a slow or steps() timing function. Without updating this data, the layout object with the animation will still have a mask based clip, but without an active animation. Because mask based clip isn't designed for shape clip paths, a crash results.



This change makes a change from having a composited clip animation to not having one unconditionally invalidate paint properties for a given LayoutObject, ensuring mask based clip stops being used when it is no longer applicable.

entry.title: Don't attempt to print pages that don't exist.
entry.content:
Due to underlying bugs [1], we may re-layout after having generated the

paginated layout, but before actually printing all the pages. If this

re-layout reduces the number of pages, we would crash, since we assumed

that the page count doesn't change under our feet (which should be a

reasonable assumption, but no). Just bail if requested to print a page

out of range.



Don't store the page count in the PrintContext object, since it may be

old news before we use it, thanks to the bugginess. Still need to store

it for plug-in contexts, though.

entry.content:
1. Freeze a11y cache as soon as the tree is complete, and before calling

back into AXReadyCallback() methods, so that they do not attempt to

alter the tree at a bad time.

Getting the computed name directly is similar to serializing, and

only retrieving the name from the serialized properties.



This avoids hitting a check in GetOrCreateAriaOwnerFor(), because

we avoid even attempting to create any accessible objects while

the tree is frozen. This was occurring while trying to GetOrCreate(node)

on a node where the AXObject had been pruned from the tree, because

in those cases we look to see if it's viable by trying to find a parent.

entry.title: [layout] Add a N-way min/max sizes cache.
entry.content:
Various layout modes (grid in particular) can query the min/max sizes

of an element multiple times with different block constraints.



For each block-constraint we might have a slightly different min/max

sizes reported.



Currently we are only able to store one min/max size result -

potentially leading to performance degradation in these cases.



This patch adds a N-way cache to help solve these problems.



First - the most common scenario is when we don't have any children

which depend on the block constraints, or our initial block-size is

indefinite.



For this case we have a special cache slot sitting on the LayoutBox

to hold these values. This case wont allocate the new MinMaxSizesCache

object.



When we have both a definite initial block-size, and children that

depend on this size, we allocate the N-way LRU cache.



This cache is small - so we just iterate over all the entries to find

the correct one - rather that something more complex than a HashMap

for example.

Upon finding an entry in the cache it'll be moved to the back.



This logic is added behind the LayoutNewMinMaxCache. With this

disabled there should be no behaviour change.

entry.title: [AsyncSB] Inject AsyncCheckTracker into BrowserUrlLoaderThrottle
entry.content:
With async Safe Browsing checks, BrowserUrlLoaderThrottle will create

two UrlCheckers, one for sync local-blocklist check, one for async

real-time check. The async check will not block UrlLoader. If the URL

loader is ready before the async checker is completed, BULT will pass

the ownership of async checker to AsyncCheckTracker.



This CL injects AsyncCheckTracker into BrowserUrlLoaderThrottle.

AsyncCheckTracker has the same lifetime as WebContents. The actual

implementation will be done in a follow-up CL.



Also introduce a feature flag SafeBrowsingAsyncRealTimeCheck to

control this feature. It is disabled by default.

entry.title: gnrt: Inherit shipped, security, and group flags consistently
entry.content:
The shipped flag and security_critical flags in the README files

are now consistent in defaulting to the group attached to the crate.



If the config specifies shipped/security_critical for the crate

itself or any ancestor of it, that overrides. If a crate is a

top level dependency (used by 1p code) then it is considered as

both shipped and security_critical by default. Otherwise, it uses

the group that is determined for the crate to set the flag. Safe

and Sandbox groups are considered both shipped+security_critical

and the Test group is considered neither.



The group resolution is based on both ancestors and dependencies:

- Ancestors can raise the privilege level. If you're used in a

Safe context, then you must be considered Safe as well. Crates

that don't have a config overriding the group but are top-level

deps of Chromium itself for 1p code default to being Safe.

- Dependencies can lower the privilege level. If you depend on

something that requires sandbox, then you also must require it.

This takes precedence over the ancestors.



`cargo -Zbindeps tree` can be used to view the dependency tree.

entry.title: Fix null reference in PaymentDetails validation
entry.content:
This fixes UBSan errors like the following:

https://luci-milo.appspot.com/ui/inv/build-8763888193215235281/test-results?q=PaymentRequestUpdateWithTest.UpdateWithModifiers&sortby=&groupby=



All the validation methods took a const PaymentItem& total parameter and

did nothing with it. But as references cannot be null, the call sites

called it with *details.total, which is undefined if the pointer is

null.



Looking at the history, the bug was introduced in

https://crrev.com/c/643768. In the old version of the file, the

parameter was const payments::mojom::PaymentItemPtr& total, which *can*

be null since it's a reference to a smart pointer. In the conversion,

this was mistranslated to a non-nullable type:



https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/643768/12/components/payments/content/payment_details_validation.cc

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/643768/12/components/payments/core/payment_details_validation.cc



We just didn't notice because the parameter was unused. The last time

the parameter was used was just before this CL:
